'''Muhammed Kerem Aktürkoğlu''' ({{IPA|tr|ceˈɾɛm akˈtyɾkoːɫu}}; born 21 October 1998) is a Turkish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[winger (association football)|winger]] or [[wide midfielder]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] and the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]].

Coming through [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|İstanbul Başakşehir]]'s youth academy, he made his debut in 2016, representing various club in the amateur Turkish [[TFF Third League]], before moving to [[Süper Lig]] club [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] in 2020 on a free transfer, where he made his professional debut and won two back-to-back league titles in [[2022–23 Süper Lig|2023]] and [[2023–24 Süper Lig|2024]]. In September 2024, he joined Benfica for a transfer fee of €12 million.

Aktürkoğlu is a former Turkey youth international, representing his country at various levels. He made his senior international debut in 2021, being chosen in Turkey's squads for two [[UEFA European Championship]]s ([[UEFA Euro 2020|2020]] and [[UEFA Euro 2024|2024]]).

==Early life==
Aktürkoğlu was born on 21 October 1998 in [[İzmit]], Turkey. At ten months old, he survived the [[1999 İzmit earthquake]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite news |last=Miller |first=Nick |date=2023-12-12 |title=Kerem Akturkoglu interview: 'People suffered in the earthquakes. You take that with you' |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5128535/2023/12/12/kerem-akturkoglu-turkey-earthquake/ |access-date=2025-04-13 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career===
Aktürkoğlu began his football career at [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|İstanbul Başakşehir]]'s youth academy,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Agencies |first=Daily Sabah with |date=2024-09-03 |title=Galatasaray sign Osimhen, sell Aktürkoğlu to Benfica in transfer flurry |url=https://www.dailysabah.com/sports/football/galatasaray-sign-osimhen-sell-akturkoglu-to-benfica-in-transfer-flurry |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=Daily Sabah |language=en-US}}</ref> signing his first professional contract with the club in 2015 at the age of 16. Despite his potential, he did not feature in any matches for Başakşehir during his four-year contract.

In 2016, he was loaned to [[BB Bodrumspor|Bodrumspor]] in the amateur [[TFF Third League]] to gain playing experience. Reflecting on his time at Başakşehir in a later interview, Aktürkoğlu expressed deep frustration, claiming that "four years of his life were stolen" due to a rigid hierarchy under [[Abdullah Avcı]] and [[Emre Belözoğlu]], where senior players exercised significant authority over younger talents. This lack of opportunities brought him to the brink of quitting football, but encouragement from his family convinced him to persevere.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |date=2022-04-29 |title=Kerem Aktürkoğlu 17 yaşındayken Başakşehir'de gördüğü psikolojik şiddeti anlattı... Olay sözler! |url=https://arsiv.turkiyegazetesi.com.tr/spor/kerem-akturkoglu-17-yasindayken-basaksehirde-gordugu-psikolojik-siddeti-anlatti-olay-sozler-854322 |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=Türkiye Gazetesi |language=tr|trans-title=Kerem Aktürkoğlu spoke about the psychological violence he experienced at Başakşehir when he was 17 years old... Scandalous words!}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite web |title=Son dakika Galatasaray haberleri: Kerem'den Başakşehir itirafı! "Babama 'futbolu bırakacağım' dedim" |trans-title=Breaking Galatasaray news: Kerem's confession about Başakşehir! "I told my father 'I'm going to quit football'" |url=https://www.sabah.com.tr/galeri/spor/son-dakika-kerem-akturkogludan-medipol-basaksehir-itirafi-babama-futbolu-birakacagim-dedim |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=Sabah |language=tr}}</ref>

In 2017, Aktürkoğlu sought a fresh start and joined fellow Turkish TFF Third League side [[Karacabey Belediyespor]] on a free transfer in search of regular playing time.<ref name=":2" /> He became a key player for his new club, featuring in 35 matches over the season and contributing three goals and two assists.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2" /> His efforts helped Karacabey reach the promotion play-offs, but the team was eliminated by Serik Belediyespor on July 15, 2019, following a narrow 4–3 aggregate loss.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2" />

After several seasons in the amateur leagues, Aktürkoğlu signed with [[24 Erzincanspor]] ahead of the 2019–20 season, another free transfer that would prove pivotal in his career.<ref name=":3">{{Cite web |last=DHA |date=2020-05-30 |title=Fenerbahçe ve Beşiktaş peşinde! Muhammet Kerem Aktürkoğlu... |url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/fenerbahce-ve-besiktas-pesinde-muhammet-kerem-akturkoglu-41528945 |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=www.hurriyet.com.tr |language=tr|trans-title=Fenerbahçe and Beşiktaş are after him! Muhammet Kerem Aktürkoğlu...}}</ref> His performances during the season improved, with a notable highlight being Erzincanspor's 2–0 victory over [[Beşiktaş J.K.|Beşiktaş]] in the [[2019–20 Turkish Cup#Fifth round|fifth round]] of the [[Turkish Cup]] on 5 December 2019.<ref name=":3" /> Over the season, Aktürkoğlu scored an impressive 20 goals in 34 matches, playing a crucial role in his team's success. In the promotion play-offs, he scored his first career hat-trick in a 4–2 semi-final win against [[Artvin Hopaspor]] on 21 July 2020, and contributed to Erzincanspor's 2–1 victory against Aksaray Bld in the final four days later, securing promotion to the [[TFF 1. Lig]].<ref name=":1" />

=== Galatasaray ===
==== 2020–2022: Record-breaking individual success and Süper Lig's Player of the Season====
On 2 September, Aktürkoğlu signed for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] on a four-year contract on a free transfer.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Hoş geldin Muhammed Kerem Aktürkoğlu |trans-title=Welcome, Muhammed Kerem Aktürkoğlu. |url=http://www.galatasaray.org/haber/futbol/hos-geldin-muhammed-kerem-akturkoglu/47059 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210604013812/https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/futbol/hos-geldin-muhammed-kerem-akturkoglu/47059 |archive-date=4 June 2021 |access-date=23 November 2020 |website=www.galatasaray.org}}</ref> He made his professional debut with Galatasaray in a 1–1 league draw against [[Kayserispor]] on 23 November 2020,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2020/11/23/turkey/super-lig/galatasaray-sk/kayserispor/3352841/|title=Galatasaray vs. Kayserispor – 23 November 2020 – Soccerway|website=uk.soccerway.com|access-date=23 November 2020|archive-date=8 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210608125826/https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2020/11/23/turkey/super-lig/galatasaray-sk/kayserispor/3352841/|url-status=live}}</ref> and scored his first goal for the club in a 3–0 win against [[Hatayspor]] on 5 December.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.haberler.com/kerem-akturkoglu-ilk-gol-sevincini-yasadi-13781371-haberi/ |title=Kerem Aktürkoğlu celebrates his first goal|website=Haberler.com|access-date=8 November 2024|date=6 April 2021}}</ref>

On 12 January 2021, having taken nearly three weeks to recover from [[COVID-19]], he returned to action against [[Antalyaspor]]; he came off the bench in the late in second half in an eventual 0–0 home draw.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.trtspor.com.tr/haber/futbol/super-lig/kerem-akturkoglunun-test-sonucu-pozitif-222529.html | title = Kerem Aktürkoğlu's test result is positive|website=Haberler.com|access-date=6 April 2021|archive-date=11 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210611162100/https://www.trtspor.com.tr/haber/futbol/super-lig/kerem-akturkoglunun-test-sonucu-pozitif-222529.html|url-status=live}}</ref> On 17 April, Aktürkoğlu scored all three goals in a 3–1 league away draw win against [[Göztepe S.K.|Göztepe]], becoming the third Turkish player to score a hat-trick for Galatasaray since [[Yasin Öztekin]] in December 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sozcu.com.tr/spor/futbol/izmirde-maca-damga-vuran-isim-kerem-akturkoglu-6379966/ |title=Kerem Aktürkoğlu, the name that left his mark on the match in İzmir! For the first time since 2016|website=Sozcu.com.tr|access-date=8 November 2024|date=6 April 2021}}</ref>

[[File:Kerem Aktürkoğlu 2021.jpg|thumb|Aktürkoğlu playing for [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] in 2021|253x253px]]
On 16 August, Aktürkoğlu was involved in a physical altercation with teammate [[Marcão (footballer, born 1996)|Marcão]] during a game against [[Giresunspor]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Galatasaray defender headbutts team-mate|language=en-GB|work=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58245066|access-date=17 August 2021|archive-date=17 August 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210817130145/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58245066|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=AA |first=DAILY SABAH WITH |date=2021-08-16 |title=Marcao assault on teammate mars Galatasaray win over Giresunspor |url=https://www.dailysabah.com/sports/football/marcao-assault-on-teammate-mars-galatasaray-win-over-giresunspor |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=Daily Sabah |language=en-US}}</ref> The fight was broken up by their teammates, before the referee of the match, Erkan Özdamar, who watched the situation after the warning of the [[video assistant referee]], sent-off Marcão. Unable to continue playing three minutes after the incident, Aktürkoğlu was taken off the field by manager [[Fatih Terim]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://arsiv.mackolik.com/Match/Default.aspx?id=3562509|title=Giresunspor 0 – 2 Galatasaray MS 16.08.2021|website=arsiv.mackolik.com|access-date=8 November 2024|date=16 August 2021}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aspor.com.tr/galatasaray/2021/08/16/giresunspor-galatasaray-macinda-kerem-akturkoglu-and-fatih-terim-arasindaki-o-konusma|title=That conversation between Kerem Aktürkoğlu and Fatih Terim during the Giresunspor Galatasaray match!|date=17 August 2021|access-date=2026-05-15|website=www.aspor.com.tr}}</ref> Two days later, the club announced that Marcão had been suspended from the squad indefinitely and he was later fined and suspended for eight-matches by the [[Turkish Football Federation]]. Before Galatasaray training started on 9 September, Marcão publicly apologized to Aktürkoğlu in front of the entire team, with the two solving their issues.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ensonhaber |date=2021-08-19 |title=PFDK, Marcao'ya 8 maç ceza verildiğini açıkladı |trans-title=The PFDK announced that Marcao has been given an 8-match ban. |url=https://www.ensonhaber.com/kralspor/pfdk-marcaoya-8-mac-ceza-verildigini-acikladi |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=Ensonhaber |language=tr}}</ref>

On 21 October, he scored his first goal in [[UEFA|European competitions]], starting and scoring in a 1–0 victory away at [[FC Lokomotiv Moscow|Lokomotiv Moscow]], in the [[UEFA Europa League]] [[2021–22 UEFA Europa League#Group stage|group stage]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=SON DAKİKA: UEFA Avrupa Ligi: Namağlup lider Galatasaray son 16 turunda |trans-title=BREAKING: UEFA Europa League: Unbeaten leader Galatasaray advances to the round of 16. |url=https://www.ntv.com.tr/spor/son-dakika-uefa-avrupa-liginamaglup-lider-galatasaray-son-16-turunda,upmHrCwpY0uHzflBza_whw |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=www.ntv.com.tr |language=tr}}</ref> On 14 March 2022, Aktürkoğlu scored a brace in a 2–1 win against [[Beşiktaş–Galatasaray rivalry|rivals]] Beşiktaş.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-03-14 |title=Galatasaray – Beşiktaş derbisinde 2 gol kaydeden Kerem Aktürkoğlu, bir ilki yaşadı |trans-title=Kerem Aktürkoğlu, who scored 2 goals in the Galatasaray – Beşiktaş derby, experienced a first. |url=https://www.cumhuriyet.com.tr/spor/galatasaray-besiktas-derbisinde-2-gol-kaydeden-kerem-akturkoglu-bir-ilki-yasadi-1915937 |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=www.cumhuriyet.com.tr |language=tr}}</ref> He finished the season, with 13 goals and 13 assists in all competitions, being named the [[2021–22 Süper Lig#Annual awards|Süper Lig Player of the Season]], as he missed only one match due to a yellow card suspension, making him the player that feature the most matches in a season in Galatasaray's history, with 52 matches played. However, Galatasaray ended the season in a disappointing 13th place, failing to qualify to any European competition.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sporx |date=2022-05-24 |title=Galatasaray için tarihin en kötü sezonu – GS Haberleri |trans-title=The worst season in history for Galatasaray – GS News |url=https://www.sporx.com/galatasaray-icin-tarihin-en-kotu-sezonu-SXHBQ974981SXQ |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=Sporx |language=tr-TR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-05-20 |title=Galatasaray'da Kerem Aktürkoğlu, Antalyaspor maçında oynarsa tarihe geçecek |trans-title=If Kerem Aktürkoğlu plays in the Antalyaspor match for Galatasaray, he will make history. |url=https://www.cumhuriyet.com.tr/spor/galatasarayda-kerem-akturkoglu-antalyaspor-macinda-oynarsa-tarihe-gececek-1937927 |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=www.cumhuriyet.com.tr |language=tr}}</ref>

==== 2022–2023: Super Lig title and rise to leadership====
On 15 December, Aktürkoğlu was named Galatasaray's [[Captain (association football)#Vice-captain|third captain]], alongside [[Fernando Muslera]] and [[Bafétimbi Gomis]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=SPORTS |first=beIN |date=2022-12-15 |title=Galatasaray da yeni kaptan Kerem Aktürkoğlu |trans-title=Galatasaray's new captain is Kerem Aktürkoğlu. |url=https://beinsports.com.tr/haber/kerem-akturkoglu-boyle-bir-sorumluluk-almak-istedim |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=beinsports.com.tr |language=tr-TR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-06 |title=Galatasaray's new captain has been determined after Kerem Aktürkoğlu's departure. |url=https://en.haberler.com/galatasaray-s-new-captain-has-been-determined-1991675/ |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=Haberler.com |language=en}}</ref> During the league break for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], he established a strong partnership with the club's new signing, [[Mauro Icardi]]. This collaboration was highlighted on 12 November when Aktürkoğlu scored a hat-trick in a 7–0 away win against his former club [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|Başakşehir]], with Icardi providing two assists for his goals.<ref>{{Cite web |title=SON DAKİKA: Başakşehir 0–7 Galatasaray (Maç sonucu) |url=https://www.ntv.com.tr/sporskor/son-dakika-basaksehir-0-7-galatasaray-mac-sonucu,U-ziyzBHtEmvsHH_g-Gh0g |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=www.ntv.com.tr |language=tr}}</ref> His prolific form continued into January 2023, he scored the second goal, assisted by Icardi, in a 3–0 victory over crosstown rivals [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] in the ''[[The Intercontinental Derby (football)|Intercontinental Derby]]'' on 8 January. This was followed by a goal in a 4–0 win against Hatayspor on 13 January and an assist in a 2–1 home win against Antalyaspor on 21 January.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |title=Fenerbahçe Galatasaray maç sonucu ne oldu, derbiyi kim kazandı? Fenerbahçe Galatasaray ilk 11'ler... |trans-title=What was the result of the Fenerbahçe vs Galatasaray match, and who won the derby? Fenerbahçe and Galatasaray starting lineups... |url=https://www.mynet.com/fb-gs-maci-canli-izleme-linki-8-ocak-fenerbahce-galatasaray-maci-saat-kacta-baslayacak-fenerbahce-galatasaray-muhtemel-11-ler-356423-myspor |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=Mynet |language=tr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://beinsports.com.tr/news/galatasaray-atakas-hatayspor-3|title=Galatasaray 4–0 Atakaş Hatayspor|date=21 January 2023|access-date=2026-05-15|website=beinsports.com.tr}}</ref>

After the league resumed in the aftermath of the [[2023 Turkey–Syria earthquake]], Aktürkoğlu picked up where he left off. On 14 April, he scored a goal and delivered two assists in a 6–0 win over Kayserispor. Four days later, he provided two more assists in a 4–1 victory against [[Alanyaspor]]. On 30 May, he recorded his first career hat-trick of assists in a 4–1 away win over [[MKE Ankaragücü|Ankaragücü]], securing Galatasaray's 23rd Süper Lig title.<ref>{{Cite web |date=May 30, 2023 |title=Turkish Super Lig: Galatasaray win title for 23th time after beating Ankaragucu 4–1 |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65761517 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230602093025/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65761517 |archive-date=2 June 2023 |access-date=May 31, 2023 |publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> The following week, he added another assist in a 3–0 away win against rivals Fenerbahçe in the reverse fixture. Aktürkoğlu finished the season with nine goals and 12 assists, earning recognition as the Süper Lig's top assist provider and a place in the league's Best XI.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mackolik.com/mac/galatasaray-vs-fenerbah%C3%A7e/1fgz5w1rv9abylv5h7dcwoftg|title=Galatasaray vs Fenerbahçe, 04.06.2023, Super League|date=6 April 2023|access-date=2026-05-15|website=www.mackolik.com}}</ref>

==== 2023–2024: Back-to-back league titles, vice-captaincy and departure====
The following [[2023–24 Galatasaray S.K. season|season]], with Bafétimbi Gomis' departure, Aktürkoğlu was promoted to vice-captain. The arrival of [[Wilfried Zaha]] saw him transition to an [[attacking midfielder|attacking midfield]] role to accommodate Zaha on the [[Left winger|left-wing]]. This positional shift led to competition with [[Dries Mertens]] for playing time, indirectly affecting his performances. Nevertheless, on 8 August, he scored his first goal of the season in a 3–0 away win against [[NK Olimpija Ljubljana|Olimpija Ljubljana]] in a [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round|2022–23 Champions League third qualifying round]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Tarihi |first=Güncelleme |date=2023-08-03 |title=Galatasaray 1–0 Zalgiris (Maç özeti) |url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/galatasaray-1-0-zalgiris-mac-ozeti-42308542 |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=www.hurriyet.com.tr |language=tr}}</ref> On 16 August, he netted twice and assisted another goal in a 4–2 home win over  [[Samsunspor]]. By 26 September, he had accumulated eight goal contributions — three goals and five assists — in his first six league matches, the highest in the league at the time.<ref>{{cite web |date=19 September 2023 |title=Kerem Aktürkoğlu inanılmazı başardı! Daha ligin başında... |trans-title=Kerem Aktürkoğlu achieved the impossible! It’s still the beginning of the season... |url=https://www.aksam.com.tr/sporplus/ne-yaptin-sen-kerem-akturkoglu-herkes-onu-konusuyor-inanilmaz/haber-1401361 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230920175633/https://www.aksam.com.tr/sporplus/ne-yaptin-sen-kerem-akturkoglu-herkes-onu-konusuyor-inanilmaz/haber-1401361 |archive-date=20 September 2023 |access-date=19 September 2023 |website=aksam.com.tr |language=tr}}</ref>

On 3 October, he scored his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goal during a 3–2 group stage victory against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] at [[Old Trafford]]. He dedicated the goal to [[Palestinians|Palestinian]]  children affected by the [[Gaza–Israel conflict]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Balkiz |first=Karya Naz |title=Galatasaray player dedicates equaliser against ManU to Palestinian children |url=https://www.trtworld.com/turkiye/galatasaray-player-dedicates-equaliser-against-manu-to-palestinian-children-16040230 |access-date=3 September 2024 |website=Galatasaray player dedicates score against Man Utd to Palestinian children}}</ref> In the return fixture on 29 November, he came off the bench to score a crucial equalizer in a 3–3 home draw against Manchester United, a strike later awarded Goal of the Week for the fifth matchday of the Champions League.<ref>{{cite web |title=Every UEFA Champions League Goal of the Week |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0285-190a07409201-a78f629e6f4d-1000--every-uefa-champions-league-goal-of-the-week/ |website=[[UEFA]] |access-date=1 December 2023 |language=en |date=29 November 2023}}</ref> On 20 December, Aktürkoğlu captained Galatasaray for the first time, scoring the only goal in a 1–0 home win over [[Fatih Karagümrük S.K.|Fatih Karagümrük]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-12-20 |title=Kerem Aktürkoğlu: Benim için gerçekten anlamlı bir geceydi |trans-title=Kerem Aktürkoğlu: It was truly a meaningful night for me. |url=https://www.trthaber.com/haber/spor/kerem-akturkoglu-benim-icin-gercekten-anlamli-bir-geceydi-822513.html |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=www.trthaber.com |language=tr}}</ref>

On 11 January 2024, he was sent off for the first time in his career, during a league match against [[Sivasspor]] for dissent after shouting at the referee, resulting in a two-match suspension. Upon his return, he scored consecutive braces against [[Trabzonspor]] on 21 January and Istanbulspor on 25 January.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kırmızı kart gören Kerem Aktürkoğlu cezalı duruma düştü |trans-title=Kerem Aktürkoğlu, who received a red card, is now suspended. |url=https://www.ntvspor.net/futbol/kirmizi-kart-goren-kerem-akturkoglu-cezali-duruma-dustu-65a012cc63b1ce005a02e7dc |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=NTVSpor.net |language=tr}}</ref> Aktürkoğlu finished the season, with 12 goals and seven assists, playing a pivotal role as Galatasaray clinched their second consecutive [[2023–24 Süper Lig|Süper Lig]] title, setting a league record of 102 points.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/40223962/galatasaray-clinch-24th-league-title-102-points-haul |title=Galatasaray clinch 24th league title after 102 points haul |publisher=ESPN |date=26 May 2024 |access-date=31 May 2024 |archive-date=31 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240531181314/https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/40223962/galatasaray-clinch-24th-league-title-102-points-haul |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Benfica===
====2024–2025: Debut season abroad====

On 3 September 2024, Aktürkoğlu joined [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] on a five-year deal for a reported fee of €12 million, with the club also receiving 10% of a future transfer, and the release clause was set at €60 million.<ref>{{cite web |date=3 September 2024 |title=Kerem Aktürkoglu é reforço do Benfica! |trans-title=Kerem Aktürkoğlu is a reinforcement for Benfica! |url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2024/09/02/futebol-benfica-kerem-akturkoglu-contratacao |work=[[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] |language=Portuguese|access-date=2026-05-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/oficial-benfica-anuncia-akturkoglu-2024090223215724159|title=Oficial: Benfica anuncia Akturkoglu|publisher=[[A Bola]]|language=Portuguese |date=2 September 2024|access-date=3 September 2024}}</ref> On 14 September, Aktürkoğlu scored on his debut for the club, netting the opener in a 4–1 home league victory over [[C.D. Santa Clara|Santa Clara]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Portugal |first=Rádio e Televisão de |date=2024-09-16 |title=Benfica goleia Santa Clara no regresso de Bruno Lage ao clube |trans-title=Benfica thrashes Santa Clara in Bruno Lage's return to the club. |url=https://www.rtp.pt/noticias/desporto/benfica-goleia-santa-clara-no-regresso-de-bruno-lage-ao-clube_v1599845 |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=Benfica goleia Santa Clara no regresso de Bruno Lage ao clube |language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=David |first=Rozehnal |date=2024-10-27 |title=tr88 |url=https://sechzigplus.net/ |access-date=2026-05-15 |website= |language=pt}}</ref> He scored again in Benfica's opening game of their [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|2024–25 Champions League]] campaign, his first goal in the competition for them, opening their 2–1 win away over [[Red Star Belgrade]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Benfica'yı öne geçiren gol Kerem Aktürkoğlu'ndan geldi! |trans-title=The goal that put Benfica ahead came from Kerem Aktürkoğlu! |url=https://www.t24.com.tr/haber/benfica-yi-one-geciren-gol-kerem-akturkoglu-ndan-geldi,1184971 |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=T24 |language=Turkish}}</ref>

On 27 October, he scored his first [[Primeira Liga]] [[hat-trick]], netting three goals in the first half of a 5–0 victory over [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave]]. In the process, he registered the most goals and assists (eight) for the club in his first seven matches reaching [[Félix Guerreiro]]'s previous record set in the [[1964–65 Primeira Liga|1964–65 season]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Esteves |first=Adérito |date=2024-10-27 |title=Benfica-Rio Ave, 5–0 Kerem magia? Chamem Hat-trick-koglu! Ou vão buscar ouro ao banco: os destaques do Benfica {{!}} Abola.pt |trans-title=Benfica-Rio Ave, 5–0 Kerem magic? Call him Hat-trick-koglu! Or go get gold from the bench: Benfica's highlights {{!}} Abola.pt |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/kerem-magia-chamem-hat-trick-koglu-ou-vao-buscar-ouro-ao-banco-os-destaques-do-benfica-2024102720282091772 |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=Abola.pt |language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=2024-10-27 |title=Aktürkoğlu, o feiticeiro que encontrou a saída da câmara dos segredos (a crónica do Benfica-Rio Ave) |url=https://observador.pt/2024/10/27/akturkoglu-o-feiticeiro-que-encontrou-a-saida-da-camara-dos-segredos-a-cronica-do-benfica-rio-ave/ |access-date=2024-10-28 |website=[[Observador]] |language=pt}}</ref> At the end of the month, he was named the league's Player of the Month and Forward of the Month for the months of September and October.<ref name="ForwardM">{{Cite web |date=2024-11-05 |title=Aktürkoglu eleito Continente Avançado do Mês Liga Portugal Betclic |trans-title=Aktürkoğlu named Continente Forward of the Month for Liga Portugal Betclic. |url=https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/epocas/20242025/noticias/geral/premios/liga-portugal-betclic/setembrooutubro/aktuerkoglu-eleito-continente-avancado-do-mes-liga-portugal-betclic/ |access-date=2024-11-07 |website=Liga Portugal |language=pt |archive-date=15 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241215185327/https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/epocas/20242025/noticias/geral/premios/liga-portugal-betclic/setembrooutubro/aktuerkoglu-eleito-continente-avancado-do-mes-liga-portugal-betclic/ |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name="PlayerM">{{Cite web |date=2024-11-05 |title=Aktürkoglu também arrecada Prémio de Jogador do Mês da Liga Portugal Betclic |trans-title=Aktürkoğlu also wins the Player of the Month Award from Liga Portugal Betclic. |url=https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/epocas/20242025/noticias/geral/premios/liga-portugal-betclic/setembrooutubro/aktuerkoglu-tambem-arrecada-premio-de-jogador-do-mes-da-liga-portugal-betclic/ |access-date=2024-11-07 |website=Liga Portugal |language=pt |archive-date=15 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241215190045/https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/epocas/20242025/noticias/geral/premios/liga-portugal-betclic/setembrooutubro/aktuerkoglu-tambem-arrecada-premio-de-jogador-do-mes-da-liga-portugal-betclic/ |url-status=dead }}</ref>

On 11 January 2025, Aktürkoğlu won his first trophy with Benfica, as they defeated [[Derby de Lisboa|crosstown rivals]] [[Sporting CP]] in the [[2025 Taça da Liga final|Taça da Liga final]] on penalties, converting Benfica's fourth penalty in the shoot-out; following a 1–1 draw in normal time.<ref name=TdLwin>{{cite web|url=https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/liga/jogo/20242025/allianzcup/3/1|title=Sporting CP 1:1 SL Benfica|website=Liga Portugal|date=11 January 2025|language=Portuguese|access-date=24 February 2025|archive-date=14 January 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250114180512/https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/liga/jogo/20242025/allianzcup/3/1|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 18 February, in the second leg of the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Knockout phase play-offs|Champions League knockout phase play-offs]], he ended his two-month goal drought, scoring the first goal in a 3–3 home draw over [[AS Monaco|Monaco]], helping his side secure a 4–3 aggregate victory to advance to the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|Champions League round of 16]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Benfica through to Champions League last 16 after heart-stopping 3–3 draw against Monaco |url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/4530-benfica-through-to-champions-league-last-16-after-heart-stopping-3-3-draw-against-monaco|access-date=20 February 2025 |website=PortuGoal}}</ref>

====2025–2026: Champions League qualification====
On 27 August 2025, Aktürkoğlu scored the only goal in a 1–0 victory over [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] in the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League qualifying|Champions League qualifying play-off round]], securing his club's place in the competition's [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League league phase|league phase]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kibrispostasi.com/c41-SPOR/n573317-kerem-akturkoglu-galibiyeti-getirdi-fenerbahceden-devler-ligine-veda |title=Kerem Aktürkoğlu galibiyeti getirdi: Fenerbahçe'den Devler Ligi'ne veda |trans-title=Kerem Aktürkoğlu brought the victory: Fenerbahçe bids farewell to the Champions League |publisher=kibrispostasi.com |language=tr |date=27 August 2025 }}</ref>

===Fenerbahçe===
On 1 September 2025, Fenerbahçe signed four-year deal with him,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2025/8/ailemize-hos-geldin-kerem-akturkoglu |title=Ailemize hoş geldin Kerem Aktürkoğlu  |publisher=Fenerbahçe S.K. |language=tr |date=1 September 2025 |access-date=16 February 2026|trans-title=Welcome to our family Kerem Aktürkoğlu}}</ref> and Benfica announced the transfer for €22.5m and adds on.<ref name="benficafener">{{cite web |url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2025/08/29/futebol-benfica-e-fenerbahce-principio-de-acordo-por-akturkoglu-transferencia |title=Benfica e Fenerbahçe: princípio de acordo por Aktürkoğlu  |publisher=S.L. Benfica |language=pt |date=29 August 2025 |trans-title=Benfica and Fenerbahçe: agreement in principle for Aktürkoğlu}}</ref> Later that month, on 14 September, he made his debut with the team in a 1–0 Süper Lig victory against [[Trabzonspor]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2025/9/fenerbahce-1-0-trabzonspor |title=Fenerbahçe 1–0 Trabzonspor |publisher=Fenerbahçe S.K. |language=tr |date=14 September 2025 |access-date=16 February 2026}}</ref> A month later, on 2 October, he scored a [[Brace (sports)|brace]] against [[OGC Nice]] in 2–1 [[2025–26 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]] group match home win.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2025/10/fenerbahce-2-1-ogc-nice |title= Fenerbahçe 2–1 OGC Nice |publisher=Fenerbahçe S.K. |language=tr |date=2 October 2025 |access-date=16 February 2026}}</ref> On 9 November, he scored his first [[Süper Lig]] goal with Fenerbahçe in 4–2 home win against [[Kayserispor]].<ref>{{cite web |url= https://fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2025/11/fenerbahce-4-2-zecorner-kayserispor |title=Fenerbahçe 4–2 Zecorner Kayserispor  |publisher=Fenerbahçe S.K. |language=tr |date=9 November 2025 |access-date=16 February 2026}}</ref>

On 9 February 2026, he scored a brace against [[Gençlerbirliği S.K.|Gençlerbirliği]] in a 3–1 Süper Lig home win.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2026/2/trabzonspor-2-3-fenerbahce |title=Trabzonspor 2-3 Fenerbahçe |publisher=Fenerbahçe S.K. |language=tr |date=14 February 2026 |access-date=16 February 2026}}</ref> Following week on 14 February 2026, Kerem scored again in 3–2 Süper Lig away win against [[Trabzonspor]] and also assisted to [[Marco Asensio]]'s winning goal.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2026/2/fenerbahce-3-1-n-d-genclerbirligi |title=Fenerbahçe 3-1 N.D. Gençlerbirliği |publisher=Fenerbahçe S.K. |language=tr |date=9 February 2026 |access-date=16 February 2026}}</ref> Later that month, on 26 February, he scored another brace in a 2–1 UEFA Europa League away won against [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2026/2/nottingham-forest-1-2-fenerbahce |title=Nottingham Forest 1-2 Fenerbahçe |website=Fenerbahce.org |date=26 February 2026 |language=tr|access-date=2026-05-15}}</ref>

==International career==
Aktürkoğlu represented [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] at [[Turkey national under-18 football team|under-18]] and [[Turkey national under-19 football team|under-19 levels]], for a total of four [[Cap (sport)|caps]]. He made his [[Turkey national football team|senior]] international debut on 27 May 2021 in a friendly against [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ESPN]]|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/lineups?gameId=596343|title=Turkey v Azerbaijan game report|date=27 May 2021|access-date=2 June 2021|archive-date=3 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210603033414/https://www.espn.com/soccer/lineups?gameId=596343|url-status=live}}</ref> On 1 June 2021, he was named in the Turkish squad for the postponed [[UEFA Euro 2020]], but did not make an appearance in an eventual group stage exit.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=35271 |title=A Millî Takımın nihai kadrosu açıklandı |trans-title=Final squad of the national team announced |work=Turkish Football Federation |date=1 June 2021 |access-date=1 June 2021 |language=tr}}</ref> He scored his first international goal on 8 October 2021 in a 1–1 home draw against [[Norway national football team|Norway]] in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]] match.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.uefa.com/european-qualifiers/match/2030916/ | title=History: Türki̇ye-Norway |access-date=2026-05-15|website=www.uefa.com}}</ref>

On 7 June 2024, he was named in Turkey's 26-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=7 June 2024 |title=A Millî Takımımızın EURO 2024 Aday Kadrosu Açıklandı |trans-title=EURO 2024 Candidate Squad of Our National Team Announced |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=44561 |language=tr |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |access-date=18 June 2024 |archive-date=7 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240607205837/https://tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=44561 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-04-13 |title=Which teams have qualified for Euro 2024? Draw, favourites, outright odds and most exciting teams |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/which-teams-have-qualified-for-euro-2024-draw-favourites-outright-odds-and-most-exciting-teams-39242744 |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref> On 18 June, he scored Turkey's third goal in a 3–1 victory against [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]] in the opening match of the European competition.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/match/2036171--turkiye-vs-georgia/|title=Türkiye 3–1 Georgia|publisher=UEFA|date=18 June 2024|access-date=18 June 2024|archive-date=18 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240618160956/https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/match/2036171--turkiye-vs-georgia/|url-status=live}}</ref> He made a further four appearances for the quarter-finalists.

On 9 September 2024, Aktürkoğlu scored his first international hat-trick against [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]] in a 3–1 win in the [[UEFA Nations League]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kerem Aktürkoğlu'ndan A Milli Takım'da ilk hat-trick |trans-title=Kerem Aktürkoğlu's first hat-trick with the national team |url=https://www.ntvspor.net/futbol/kerem-akturkoglu-ndan-a-milli-takim-da-ilk-hat-trick-66df5e85f3d057042f45d1ce |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=NTVSpor.net |language=tr}}</ref> On 31 March 2026, he scored the only goal in a 1–0 away win over [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]] in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA second round#Path C|2026 FIFA World Cup European play-off final]], qualifying his nation to the World Cup for the first time since [[2002 FIFA World Cup|2002]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dailysabah.com/sports/football/turkiye-beat-kosovo-to-qualify-for-2026-fifa-world-cup |title=Türkiye beat Kosovo to qualify for 2026 FIFA World Cup |publisher=Daily Sabah |date=31 March 2026 |access-date=2026-05-15}}</ref>

==Player profile==
===Style of play===
Primarily a [[left winger]], he has adapted to other roles, including  [[attacking midfielder]] or [[second striker]]. His dribbling, agility, and ball control enable him to outmaneuver defenders and create chances in tight spaces. He cuts inside to shoot or delivers incisive passes, exploiting defensive gaps. His pace and precision make him a counterattacking threat, stretching defenses and delivering accurate crosses with both feet.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-10-11 |title=Arsenal and Tottenham impressed as they scout winger against Manchester United |url=https://dailycannon.com/2023/10/arsenal-tottenham-eye-galatasaray-winger-kerem-akturkoglu/ |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=dailycannon.com |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://totalfootballanalysis.com/player-analysis/forwards-202324-scout-report-tactical-analysis-tactics|title=League-leap Prospects: 3 Forwards Primed For Europe's Football Powerhouses – Scout Report|date=23 February 2024|access-date=2026-05-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thescoutingapp.com/blog/scouting-report-kerem-akt-uuml-rkoglu-208|title=Scouting Report: Kerem Aktürkoglu|date=23 February 2024|access-date=2026-05-15}}</ref>

===Goal celebration===
Aktürkoğlu adopted his ''Expelliarmus'' [[goal celebration]] in response to the nickname "Kerem Potter," given by fans in July 2021 after he shared an Instagram photo wearing round glasses and Galatasaray's red and yellow kit, resembling [[Harry Potter]]'s [[Gryffindor]] uniform. Fans flooded the post with wand and lightning emojis, inspiring Aktürkoğlu to embrace the persona. He debuted the celebration on 25 December 2021, during a match against Fenerbahçe, mimicking a spell-casting motion from the Harry Potter series. The gesture delighted fans and reinforced his "Kerem Potter" identity, earning him the nickname "the magician" in during matches.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Cunningham |first=Sam |date=2022-04-01 |title=Meet the Turkish wizard they call Harry Potter whose magic is attracting Premier League clubs |url=https://inews.co.uk/sport/football/kerem-akturkoglu-galatasaray-harry-potter-magic-arsenal-tottenham-premier-league-transfer-1549869 |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=The i Paper |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/akturkoglu-mostra-que-merece-a-alcunha-de-harry-potter-2024110420203607983?srsltid=AfmBOooiIhXxzrniIwfJWIGGqdPyMgZbplM5yGiRcLSFUnYk1z7n1RXN|title="Akturkoglu shows he deserves the nickname Harry Potter"|date=5 November 2024|access-date=2026-05-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/en-us/agora/noticias/2024/09/03/futebol-benfica-entrevista-kerem-akturkoglu-contratacao-reforco?srsltid=AfmBOopY1w_oA4bUMkYdvMKfgjgPRcsA1z-FwKyQDk9xpTlK1XssPusJ|title="I promise the fans that I'll always give 100 percent on the pitch"|date=3 September 2024|access-date=2026-05-15}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Aktürkoğlu is a practicing [[Muslims|Muslim]], and made the [[Umrah]] pilgrimage to [[Mecca]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-09-07 |title=Kerem Aktürkoğlu umre ziyaretiyle ilgili duygularını paylaştı |url=https://www.trthaber.com/haber/spor/kerem-akturkoglu-umre-ziyaretiyle-ilgili-duygularini-paylasti-793866.html |access-date=3 September 2024 |website=www.trthaber.com |language=tr}}</ref> In September 2024, Aktürkoğlu started his own [[Kick (service)|Kick]] channel, under his surname Akturkoglu, uploading gaming streams and fan [[Interview|Q&As]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fotospor.com/futbol/keremdan-farkli-bir-roportaj-627233/|title=A different interview from Kerem|access-date=11 November 2024|date=19 December 2023}}</ref>

He provided both financial and moral support to victims of the [[2023 Turkey–Syria earthquake]]. Actively participating in the "We Are Together" campaign, he encouraged citizens to host displaced individuals, especially in [[Hatay]], one of the hardest-hit Turkish regions. He also donated the match ball from his hat-trick against [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|Başakşehir]] to an auction, with the proceeds aiding earthquake recovery efforts in his home country.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Galatasaray oyuncusu Kerem Aktürkoğlu, Gölcük'te enkazdan çıktı; şimdi Hatay'a yardıma koşuyor |trans-title=Galatasaray player Kerem Aktürkoğlu emerged from the rubble in Gölcük; now he is rushing to help in Hatay. |url=https://www.ntvspor.net/foto-galeri/golcuk-te-enkazdan-cikti-simdi-hatay-a-yardima-kosuyor-63e3ef090d0b57102060f8f4/1 |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=NTVSpor.net |language=tr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Kerem-akturkoglu-le-miracule-qui-espere-porter-la-turquie-face-au-portugal/1323932 | title=Qualif. CM : Kerem Aktürkoglu, le miraculé qui espère porter la Turquie face au Portugal |access-date=2026-05-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.cnnturk.com/spor/futbol/erden-timur-ve-kerem-akturkoglu-hataya-gitti | title=Erden Timur ve Kerem Aktürkoğlu Hatay'a gitti – Son Dakika Futbol Haberi | date=8 February 2023 |access-date=2026-05-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/galatasarayli-kerem-akturkoglu-hat-trick-yaptigi-mactaki-topu-depremzedeler-icin-bagisladi-42222234 | title=Galatasaraylı Kerem Aktürkoğlu, hat-trick yaptığı maçtaki topu depremzedeler için bağışladı | date=19 February 2023 |access-date=2026-05-15}}</ref>

